{
  "text": "Majority had improvement in symptoms of prolapse, quality of life, urogenital symptoms, and minimal recurrence of POP (Table 5) . Regarding the demographic profile of women with POP, it was common in postmenopausal with higher parity index more than four. In a study done by Chhetry et al, [CITATION_1] the mean age of women with occurrence of POP was 28 years. In another study, [CITATION_2] third degree POP (38.6%) was commonest among all POP cases and maximum numbers of women with POP (65%) were multipara.",
